headlines.description: Joel Berry II had 27 points, Luke Maye had 24 points and a career-high 17 rebounds and No. 13 North Carolina defeated Davidson 85-75 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Berry, Maye carry No. 13 UNC past pesky Davidson 85-75

headlines.description: Killian Tillie scored 22 points and Zach Norvell Jr. added 21 points, all in the second half, as No. 15 Gonzaga came back to beat No. 25 Creighton 91-74 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tillie, Norvell lift No. 15 Zags over No. 25 Creighton 91-74

headlines.description: Ryan Funk scored 22 points, Aleksander Dozic added a career-high 19 and Marist hit 12 3-pointers in the second half to erase a 20-point deficit and defeat The Citadel 100-91 in the Bulldog Bash on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Marist erases 20-point deficit, defeats The Citadel 100-91

headlines.description: Tommy Funk had 16 points and six assists, Jordan Fox added 13 points and Army defeated UMBC 81-70 at the Bulldog Bash on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Funk scores 16, Army defeats UMBC 81-70

headlines.description: Ryan Luther scored 16 points and grabbed nine rebounds and Pittsburgh pulled away late for a 76-64 victory over Duquesne in the annual City Game on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luther leads Pittsburgh to 76-64 win over Duquesne

headlines.description: Isaac Haas scored 21 points, Dakota Mathias added 20 and Purdue opened defense of its Big Ten regular season title by holding off Maryland 80-75 Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haas scored 21 as Purdue holds on to beat Maryland 80-75

headlines.description: Mike Laster scored 18 points on 8-of-12 shooting and Doug Taylor helped Ohio dominate the boards with 10 rebounds in an 80-37 victory over winless Coppin State on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Laster leads Ohio past Coppin State 80-37

headlines.description: David DiLeo made 3 of 6 from 3-point range and scored 19, and Central Michigan held on to win its fifth straight on Friday night, 70-63 over Jackson State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Central Michigan holds off Jackson State 70-63

headlines.description: Blake Francis scored 19 points and hit two free throws with three seconds left in the game to help Wagner hold off Fairfield 78-76 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Francis helps Wagner fend off Fairfield 78-76

headlines.description: Bryce Dulin scored a career-high 30 points with 8-for-12 shooting to lead Navy to an 82-76 win over Delaware on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Navy holds off Delaware rally for 82-76 win

headlines.description: Luke Doyle scored 13, Divine Myles had 12 points, five rebounds and six assists, and Stetson beat NAIA member Edward Waters 85-52 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stetson beats NAIA Edward Waters 85-52

headlines.description: Andre Fox had 14 points and four assists, Justyn Mutts added 10 points, five rebounds and three blocked shots and High Point ran away from Johnson & Wales (N.C.) 90-54 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: High Point pummels Johnson & Wales (NC) 90-54

headlines.description: Diontae Jones had 18 points and nine rebounds Friday night when a Georgia Tech player inadvertently tipped a shot into the wrong basket with 6.5 seconds left to send Grambling State to a 64-63 upset win over the Yellow Jackets.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ga. Tech's own basket costly vs. Grambling St.

headlines.description: Joseph Kilgore scored 18 points on 8-of-11 shooting and handed out six assists to help Texas A&M-Corpus Christi snap a five-game skid with an 80-42 win over Division III Texas Lutheran on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Texas A&M-CC beats Division III Texas Lutheran 80-42

headlines.description: Johnathan Stove hit 11 of 12 free throws and scored 23 to lead six players in double figures and added seven assists and six rebounds to power Louisiana to a 105-80 win over Nicholls on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Louisiana owns Nicholls in second half for 105-80 win

headlines.description: Elijah Childs scored 14 points to go with nine rebounds, Dwayne Lautier-Ogunleye got his first career double-double and Bradley slipped past Eastern Illinois 67-56 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bradley cruises to 67-5 win over Eastern Illinois

headlines.description: Maurice Howard set career highs with seven 3-pointers and 23 points, and Alcorn State dominated the final 25 minutes to beat NAIA Rust College 89-50 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alcorn State handles NAIA Rust College 89-50

headlines.description: Scottie Lindsey scored five of his game-high 22 points in overtime and Northwestern trailed for much of the evening before pulling out a 72-68 victory over Illinois on Friday night in the Big Ten opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northwestern outlasts Illinois in overtime, 72-68

headlines.description: Jared Stutzman scored a career-high 20 points on 7-for-10 shooting to lead Idaho State to its first victory of the season, 92-71 over Bethesda on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Idaho State gets first win of the season 92-71 over Bethesda

headlines.description: Lexus Williams hit a 3-pointer from half-court at the buzzer to lift Boise State to a 73-70 victory over Oregon on Friday night and snap the nation's longest home winning streak.

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
